==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*geldan''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[gelda]], Old Saxon [[geldan]] (Dutch [[gelden]]), Old High German [[geltan]] (German [[gelten]]), Old Norse [[gjalda]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'jieldan/

===Verb===
'''ġieldan''' (class III strong)
# to [[pay]]; to give something in payment or as due
# to [[repay]], to pay back, to [[restore]]
# to [[requite]]; to [[reward]]

===Descendents===
*English [[yield]]

